  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Persecuted, but not forsaken,.... Pursued from place to place, and followed with menaces, curses, and reproaches; laid hold on, proscribed, imprisoned, and threatened with the severest tortures, and death itself; but our God never leaves us nor forsakes us; though we are followed close by evil men, and left by our friends, we are not forsaken of God: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "cast down we sometimes are, as an earthen vessel; 2 Corinthians 4:7, which may be cast out of a man's hands, in order to be dashed to pieces; or as a man in wrestling, see Ephesians 6:12 may be thrown to the ground by his antagonist, so we are sometimes foiled by sin, Satan, and the world: ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "cast down we sometimes are, as an earthen vessel; ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2 Corinthians 4:7",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ", which may be cast out of a man's hands, in order to be dashed to pieces; or as a man in wrestling, see ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Ephesians 6:12",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " may be thrown to the ground by his antagonist, so we are sometimes foiled by sin, Satan, and the world: ",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "but not destroyed; we are still safe in the hands of Christ, and are kept by the power of God; and, indeed, to what else can all this be ascribed? it is surprising that earthen vessels should bear and suffer so much, and not fall, or be dashed to pieces. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "but not destroyed; we are still safe in the hands of Christ, and are kept by the power of God; and, indeed, to what else can all this be ascribed? it is surprising that earthen vessels should bear and suffer so much, and not fall, or be dashed to pieces. ",
